Reasoning: The paper discusses wireless networks and their optimization using scheduling and decentralized operation, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of large antenna-arrays and channel-reciprocity based downlink transmission suggests a focus on Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM). The use of Poisson Point Process (PPP) problem formulation and simulations suggest a focus on Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
